## Goals

* Receive analog signals from 5 hydrophones
* Filter those 5 signals
* amplify the signal and recalibrate it to 0-3.3V
* Send those clean signal to the FPGA
* Secure the PCB

## Strategic approach

We want asimple, efficientPCBto adapt the signal from the 5 hydrophones to the FPGA. The FPGAneedsa signal range of 0-3.3V. After several tests, we found out the voltageoutputfrom the hydrophones, which is between 10 to 30 mV. Knowing that, we need an op-amp with a gain of around 100.By doing so, we will need a 3V3 anda-3V3 voltage supply. After that, we need an op-amp to recalibrate the signal from +20mV to 0-3.3V. We decided to also puta band filterto clean the signal a little bit, even when it's notnecessarybecause we were doing some digital filter either. We finally want good and secure connectors, one way, and quick connect.

## Hardware requirements

<colgroup><col /><col /><col /><col /></colgroup>|#|Title|Importance|Notes|
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
|1|Band pass filter|Low|<ul><li>ButterWorth 4th</li></ul>|
|2|Amplification|High|<ul><li>x100 gain</li><li>offset for a signal range of 0-3.3V</li></ul>|
|3|Connector|Medium|<ul><li>Right angle, through a hole</li><li>one way connect</li><li>ESD protection</li></ul>|
|4|Supply|High|<ul title=""><li>Make a 3.3V from LDO</li><li>Make a -3.3V from a charge pump</li></ul>|
|11|PCB layout|Medium|<ul><li>Respect thermal dissipation to prevent overheating</li><li>Must not exceed 10 x 10 cm</li></ul>|
|12|Size|Medium|<ul><li>Must fit in top of the power PCB</li><li>Careful with the height of the components</li></ul>|
|14|Mounting holes|Medium|<ul><li>M2 hole to mount on top of PCB power</li></ul>|
|15|Components size|High|<ul><li>Big enough to disperse heat</li><li><span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);">Use 0805 surface mount components</span></li></ul>|
